Female genitalia
(
Fig. 87
) with a membranous, spherical corpus bursae. Signum developed as a characteristically paired triangular sclerite, medially less sclerotized, at the anterior part of corpus bursae (
Fig. 86b
). Ductus bursae with sclerotized posterior part connected to the funnel-shaped antrum. Posterior apophyses twice length of anterior apophyses.
